ty (gridiron football position)|safety]] [[Duron Harmon]] and a seventh-round pick from the [[New England Patriots]] in exchange for a fifth-round pick in the [[2020 NFL Draft]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.detroitlions.com/news/lions-acquire-s-duron-harmon-via-trade-with-new-england-patriots |title=Lions acquire S Duron Harmon via trade with New England Patriots |work=Detroit Lions |date=March 18, 2020 |accessdate=March 18, 2020}}</ref>\n*On March 19, the Lions traded [[cornerback]] [[Darius Slay]] to the [[Philadelphia Eagles]] in exchange for a third-round pick and a fifth-round pick in the 2020 NFL Draft.<ref name=Slay>{{cite web |url=http://www.nfl.com/news/story/0ap3000001106944/article/eagles-trading-for-darius-slay-cb-gets-extension |title=Eagles trading for Darius Slay; CB gets extension |website=NFL.com |first=Kevin |last=Patra |date=March 19, 2020 |accessdate=March 19, 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Draft===\n{{main|2020 NFL Draft}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|+ style=\"{{NFLPrimaryStyle|Detroit Lions|year=2020|border=2}}\"| 2020 Detroit Lions Draft\n|-\n! Round !! Selection !! Player !! Position !! College !! Notes !! Source\n|-\n! [[List of Detroit Lions first-round draft picks|1]] || 3\n| [[Jeff Okudah]] || [[Cornerback|CB]] || [[Ohio State Buckeyes football|Ohio State]] || <!--NOTE--> || <ref>[https://www.detroitlions.com/news/detroit-lions-draft-cornerback-jeff-okudah Lions draft cornerback Jeff Okudah ] NFL.com, April 23, 2020</ref>\n|-\n! 2 || 35\n| [[D'Andre Swift]] || [[Running Back|RB]] || [[Georgia Bulldogs football|Georgia]] || <!--NOTE--> || <ref>[https://www.detroitlions.com/news/detroit-lions-draft-running-back-d-andre-swift Lions draft running back D'Andre Swift] NFL.com, April 24, 2020</ref>\n|-\n! rowspan=2| 3 || 67\n| [[Julian Okwara]] || [[Defensive end|DE]] || [[Notre Dame Fighting Irish football|Notre Dame]] || <!--NOTE-->|| <ref>[https://www.mlive.com/lions/2020/04/2020-nfl-draft-detroit-lions-select-edge-julian-okwara-with-first-of-2-third-round-picks.html 2020 NFL draft: Detroit Lions select Notre Dame EDGE Julian Okwara with first of 2 third-round picks] MLive.com, April 24, 2020</ref>\n|-\n! 75\n| [[Jonah Jackson]] || [[Guard (gridiron football)|G]] || [[Ohio State Buckeyes football|Ohio State]] || from [[2020 Indianapolis Colts season|Indianapolis]] || <ref>[https://www.mlive.com/lions/2020/04/2020-nfl-draft-detroit-lions-trade-up-for-ohio-state-g-jonah-jackson-in-third-round.html 2020 NFL draft: Detroit Lions trade up for Ohio State G Jonah Jackson in third round] MLive.com, April 24, 2020</ref>\n|-\n! 4 || 121\n| [[Logan Stenberg]] || [[Guard]] || [[Kentucky Wildcats football|Kentucky]] || From [[2020 Las Vegas Raiders season|Las Vegas]]|| <!--Source-->\n|-\n!  rowspan=2| 5 || 166\n| <!--PLAYER--> || <!--POSITION--> || <!--COLLEGE--> || <!--NOTE-->|| <!--Source-->\n|-\n!  172\n| <!--PLAYER--> || <!--POSITION--> || <!--COLLEGE--> || From Las Vegas||<!--Source-->\n|-\n! 6 || 197\n| <!--PLAYER--> || <!--POSITION--> || <!--COLLEGE--> || from Indianapolis|| <!--Source-->\n|-\n! 7 || 235\n| <!--PLAYER--> || <!--POSITION--> || <!--COLLEGE--> || from [[2020 New England Patriots season|New England]]|| <!--Source-->\n|}\n'''Draft Day Trades'''\n*The Lions traded pick numbers 85, 149, and 182 to the [[Indianapolis Colts|Indianapolis]] for picks numbers 75 and 197.\n* The Lions traded pick number 109 to the Las Vegas Raiders for pick numbers 121 and 172\n'''Notes'''\n*On August 23, 2018, the Lions traded a conditional seventh-round selection to the [[San Francisco 49ers]] in exchange for [[linebacker]] [[Eli Harold]].<ref>{{cite web|title=trade! Lions acquire LB Eli Harold from 49ers|url=http://www.nfl.com/news/story/0ap3000000950252/article/lions-acquire-linebacker-eli-harold-from-49ers|author=Sessler, Marc|website=NFL.com|date=August 23, 2018}}</ref>\n*On October 22, 2019, the Lions traded [[safety (gridiron football position)|safety]] [[Quandre Diggs]] and a seventh-round pick 